The paper deals with image recognition systems and their training using webly supervised data. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. However, the paper also involves the use of user comments and language modeling, indicating that it could also belong to the Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) and Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories. The development of new loss functions and feed-forward convolutional networks suggests that the paper could also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves phrase-based image retrieval and zero-shot transfer, which could place it in the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
